-- Chilean Stocks: Banco de Chile, Corpbanca Retreat; Lan Advances
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2011-12-22T20:38:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/chilean-stocks-banco-de-chile-corpbanca-retreat-lan-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index closed little changed at 4,199.64. The  MSCI
Chile (MXCL)  index gained 0.8 percent to 2,274.48.  Banco de Chile  (CHILE CC), the country’s second-largest
lender, fell 0.9 percent to 69.64 pesos. The central bank said
it will hold 91-day repurchase operations twice a week until
February to help ease a liquidity squeeze in pesos, after yields
on short-term debt in Chile soared.  Corpbanca (CORPBANC)   retreated 0.6 percent to 7 pesos.
Chile’s fifth-largest lender by assets was placed yesterday on
review for a possible downgrade of its  credit rating  by  Standard
& Poor’s , which cited potential deterioration of asset quality
from its planned purchase of Banco Santander SA’s operations in
Colombia.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   rose 0.2 percent to 12,399 pesos.
Latin America’s largest airline by market value rose for a fifth
consecutive session after shareholders approved yesterday the
takeover of Brazil’s  Tam SA. (TAMM4)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
